reviews.text: Would be nice to have toilets open, at least to customers. On the other side, the new ticket machine has a help desk call ready through which you can speak with real, and helpful person.

It's a bit of a pain to walk down the steps to the street and it's served by trains that can be longer than the platforms themselves (this has caught out passengers in the past.) Not alot of seating on Platform 2 either. North Camp Station is a bit of a walk away.
Really interesting & unusual station to explore. Nice views from platforms. The help points actually work (unusual for SWT).

Just about does the job of being a place for trains to stop. The standard of station up keep is well below what any reasonable person would expect. Station is for the most part very dirty, lacks facilities. Ticket office is only part time and even manages to open less than the posted opening times.
Its good but no customer assistance when stuck
